cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with resource allocation in a UAV-assisted small-cell network, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a novel utility-aware resource-allocation protocol, which involves optimization of information transmission and processing, making it relevant to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the design and optimization of a system comprising UAVs and small cells, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers heterogeneous users with different data rates and coverage demands, which are relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper proposes an iterative feasibility checking method for obtaining the global optimal resource allocation policy, which involves game-theoretic concepts.
